WikiForge-managed LLM Wiki. Knowledge in `wiki/`, sources in `raw/`,
agents in `.forge/agents/`, skills in `.forge/skills/`.

## Structure

- `wiki/` — LLM-maintained knowledge (entities, concepts, sources, comparisons)
- `raw/` — Immutable source documents
- `outputs/` — Generated deliverables
- `.forge/agents/` — Agent personas with SKILL.md and capabilities menus
- `.forge/skills/{phase}/` — Workflows organized by wiki lifecycle phase
- `.forge/config.yaml` — Runtime configuration
- `.forge/_config/` — Manifests (skill, agent, file catalogs)
- `.cursor/skills/` — IDE launchers

> `outputs/` is a render target — deliverables are views rendered from wiki content. The wiki is canonical.

> Agents are personas, not separate runtimes. One LLM session adopts whichever agent role the user invokes.

